<p style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:bold;color:#0F2D57;margin:0 0 12px 0;">Executive Summary</p>
<p style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#1A1A1A;line-height:1.6;margin:0 0 10px 0;">Regional infrastructure developments — notably the G42–du–Microsoft collaboration in Abu Dhabi — expand locally hosted cloud capacity and create immediate opportunities for public‑sector and partner‑led AI deployments in the UAE.</p>
<p style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#1A1A1A;line-height:1.6;margin:0 0 10px 0;">At the platform level, Microsoft's MAI multimodal models and ongoing Copilot feature cadence make multimodal and productivity scenarios increasingly enterprise‑ready, while adoption will be shaped by PDPL and regional hosting/governance requirements that sellers must address up front.</p>
<p style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#1A1A1A;line-height:1.6;margin:0;">Shifting hyperscaler market shares and Gartner's iPaaS Leader placement provide commercial leverage: emphasise Azure hybrid and governance capabilities (Azure Arc/Azure Stack) and cite analyst recognition during RFPs, POCs and procurement conversations to accelerate short‑listing and conversion.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>

